 Dr. Dre American rapper Dr Dre has finally been released from hospital after suffering a brain aneurysm. TMZ reports, the music mogul was discharged on Friday and will be monitored 24 hours a day by medical professionals, at home. This is coming weeks after he was hospitalised after suffering a brain aneurysm. The music mogul was hospitalised on Monday, January 4, 2021. In the early hours of Wednesday, January 6, 2021, the rapper took to his Instagram page where he revealed that he was doing fine. “Thanks to my family, friends, and fans for their interest and well wishes. I’m doing great and getting excellent care from my medical team. I will be out of the hospital and back home soon. Shout out to all the great medical professionals at Cedars. One Love!!” he wrote.